></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">During your Ghorepani Poon Hill\r\ntrek, you will be staying at locally made tea Houses and Lodges. On this trek,\r\nthe accommodation will be private with twin beds and private lockers. You will\r\nhave a comfortable mattress, pillows, small tea table, and Blanket in your room\r\nbut the bathroom is not there inside. It is sharing and if you use a hot shower\r\nthey will charge extra.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The price of Accommodation during\r\nthe Ghorepani Poon hill trek is about 5 to $10 US (twin bedroom).<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Is there electricity to charge my\r\ncamera and phone?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Yes, there are many places where you\r\ncan charge all your electronic devices. You have to bring all your cable or\r\ncharger yourself. You are suggested to keep your entire electronic devices warm\r\ninside the sleeping bag or blanket because the cold temperature drains\r\nbatteries very quickly.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">How hard is Ghorepani Poon Hill\r\nTrekking?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The Ghorepani Poon hill trekking is\r\nprobably the easy trek in the Annapurna region of Nepal. Every day the trekking\r\ndistance from one settlement to the Next is Different however, usually, you\r\nhave to walk 4 to 6 hours a day. If you are simply fit physically and mentally\r\nyou can make it.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">It is 4 days walking holiday but only\r\nthe first 2 days will be ascending through the forest of rhododendron and the 2\r\nlast days is just descending through the forest and Villages.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">What kind of foods are available\r\nduring the Ghorepani Poon hill trek?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">While trekking in the Annapurna\r\nGhorepani area, your breakfast and Dinner will be served from the lodge\r\nsimilarly, your lunch provides by a local inn or Restaurant.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The Dhalbhat (Served with rice,\r\ncurry, spinach, Lentil soup, pickle&amp; Pappadam) is the name of Nepali food\r\nwhich is really popular in the mountains. Furthermore, you can have bread, set\r\nbreakfast (served with bread, omelet, potatoes &amp; Tea), Fried Noodles, fry\r\nrice, Mo: Mo (Dumpling food), the variety of soups, Ramayan Korean soup, Indian\r\ndishes, however, you can have almost all kind food but don’t expect professionally\r\ncooked food. It is simply made fresh and safe to eat.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Drinks are available too in the\r\nlodge and restaurant booths.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Is Ghorepani trek risky from AMS\r\n(acute mountain sickness)?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Ghorepani Poon Hill trek is an easy\r\nand low-altitude trek. The highest spot you will spend your night at\r\nGhorepani&nbsp; (2,028 m), so during this short and easy trek, there are no\r\nchances to get High Altitude Mountain sickness. Usually, people might get\r\naltitude sickness after crossing 3500 meters.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">If I get sick during this trek what\r\ndo I need to do?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">If you are trekking alone, you can\r\nshare your problem with the Hotel owner or with your nearest friend around you\r\nsimilarly, if you are trekking with a trekking guide, you can tell your problem\r\nwith him, and he will help you. If you have a general problem, he will advise\r\nyou to use medicine but if you have a serious problem he will arrange an\r\nemergency helicopter evacuation.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">What is the weather and climate\r\nsituation in Poon Hill?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The weather and climate will depend\r\non the season, there are 4 different seasons, however, Poon hill is a cold and\r\nwindy view spot, thus you have to bring warm clothes with you such as a warm\r\nHat, warm jacket, Gloves, headlight, and some snacks.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The weather gets really clear during\r\nOctober and November (autumn season) likewise March to May (spring season), so\r\nthe autumn season and spring seasons are known as the best trekking season in\r\nNepal including Ghorepani Poon hill. Furthermore, if you wish to explore Poon\r\nhill during the monsoon or winter that is absolutely possible, but the view can\r\nbe on and off every day.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">What is roughly the price of the\r\nGhorepani Poon hill trek?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">The cost usually depends on the\r\nservices you are getting, but usually, for 4 nights 5 days package price costs\r\n$490 US.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">How much to hire a Guide and Porter\r\na day?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">To hire a guide for the Poon hill\r\ntrek costs $25 US and $20 US for a porter a day. The next,&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Guide and Porter</span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;salary might be a little lesser during Winter and\r\nmonsoon season.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">When is the best time for the Poon\r\nhill trek?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Poon hill trek is suitable during\r\nSpring because the Poon hill trek route is almost through the rhododendron\r\nforest every day and spring is the time in blooms and clear sky in the\r\nbackground, thus the best trekking time for Poon hill is spring season (March\r\nto May).<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 6.65pt 0in 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:101.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">What is the shortest time to finish\r\nthe Poon hill trek?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 3.35pt; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">If you are really tight on the\r\nschedule, then 4 days will be enough from Kathmandu to Kathmandu, but if you\r\nare in Pokhara then two days’ time will be enough. The fact is that for a few\r\nyears you can use jeep service straight to Nangethati which means you can skip\r\n1 full day of walking already and two days will be enough from Pokhara to\r\nPokhara.</span></p>', 'Poon hill trek 3 days offer spectacular Annapurna panoramic view from Ghorepani Poon hill (3210 m /10528 ft). The Poon hill trek 3 days trail passes the traditional Magar village and largest Rhododendron forest in the Annapurna region. Poon Hill trek is designed for those who have very limited time and eager to explore wilderness trekking in a short time. This trek is the most popular group trek, while you can see wonderful typical village life and a short trek. As a result, the trekking is easy and safe for all age group trekkers.', '28.4002,83.6893', '2', 'April to November', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/10/20', '2021/10/29', '2021/10/18', 'https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d14038.526016923412!2d83.68052236787902!3d28.400195868784877!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3995fb901538e619%3A0x8c8090bd893ea23a!2sPoon%20Hill!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1635418146598!5m2!1sen!2sin', '<p style=\"margin-top:10.2pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:10.2pt;margin-left:\r\n0in;background:#F8F8F8;vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;\r\nfont-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;color:#666666\">Day 01: Arrival at\r\nTribhuvan International Airport in Kathmandu. Meet &amp; Greet from our\r\nrepresentative and transfer to hotel &amp; overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10.2pt 0in; background: rgb(248, 248, 248); vertical-align: baseline; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Day 02: After breakfast full day sightseeing of Kathmandu\r\nincluding of Bouddhanath, Pashupatinath and Bhaktapur Durbar Square. Back to\r\nhotel &amp; overnight stay.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10.2pt 0in; background: rgb(248, 248, 248); vertical-align: baseline; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Day 03: Drive to Phedi via Pokhara for the Annapurna Base Camp\r\ntrekking. 1 hour trek to Dhampus for dinner overnight stay at Tea House Lodge.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10.2pt 0in; background: rgb(248, 248, 248); vertical-align: baseline; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Day 04: Trek Dhampus to Ghanndruk. Lunch on the way to trekking\r\nat Deurali. Dinner &amp; overnight at Tea House Lodge in Ghandruk.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10.2pt 0in; background: rgb(248, 248, 248); vertical-align: baseline; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Day 05: Few hours trek get you to Tadapani in between dense\r\nforest, rest Lunch, dinner &amp; rest time at Local Lodge.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10.2pt 0in; background: rgb(248, 248, 248); vertical-align: baseline; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:&quot;Helvetica&quot;,&quot;san