(6, 8, '8 days POKHARA  CHITWAN (US$.550)', '8-days-POKHARA-CHITWAN-(US$.550)', 'package-main-photo-61b07ed2ddfe4.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><a href=\"https://www.nepalpackagetour.com/tour/kathmandu-pokhara-chitwan-tour#multiCollapseOne50\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, &quot;sans-serif&quot;;\"><o:p></o:p></span></a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">How far is Chitwan from\r\nPokhara?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">Chitwan National Park is\r\nlocated in the western Terai of Nepal, 84 kilometres from Pokhara. Although it\r\nis not on the most direct route between Pokhara and Kathmandu, it is\r\nequidistant from either city, making it convenient for detours when travelling\r\nin Nepal.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">How to get Chitwan from\r\nPokhara?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">By bus • 4h 30m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">1. Fly from Pokhara to Bhadrapur to reach Chitwan.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">2. Take the bus or car from Pokhara to Chitwan<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">How long is the journey\r\nfrom Kathmandu to Chitwan?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">About five hours by private transfer.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">On a good day, the overland drive between Kathmandu and\r\nChitwan National Park takes about five hours. It\'s a scenic drive that follows\r\nthe Trisuli Valley, with its steep forested hills and farming villages, for a\r\nlong distance, then turns south into Mugling and the plains.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">&nbsp;How far is Pokhara\r\nfrom Kathmandu?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">126 miles<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">Pokhara doesn\'t seem very far from Kathmandu (the city\r\nis only 205 km), but the road\'s quality makes for a very long journey. For this\r\nreason, many travellers choose to fly. Here are your options for travelling\r\nbetween the two cities, either by air or by road.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, '28.2096,83.9856', '3', 'APR OCT NOV', 'Adventurous', '02nd April 2022', '2022/04/02', '2022/04/02', '2022/03/01', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d496113.92041601305!2d100.3529071711315!3d13.72510879354118!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x311d6032280d61f3%3A0x10100b25de24820!2sBangkok%2C+Thailand!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sbd!4v1544191664761\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; text-align: left;\">Day 01: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrive KATHMANDU</span><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">Arrive\r\nKathmandu and meet assistance at the airport and transfer to Hotel Grand. &nbsp;Afternoon half day sightseeing visiting\r\nSwoyambhu Temple. O/nt. At Hotel Grand.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 02: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore KATHMANDU</span><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">Early\r\nmorning at 05:00 AM drive to the domestic airport for Mountain flight for about\r\none hour. After return back to hotel, have breakfast and get ready for Full day\r\n&nbsp;sightseeing of Kathmandu Valley\r\nvisiting, Pashupatinath Temple, Boudha Stupa, Budanilkanta (Sleeping Vishnu) and Kathmandu\r\ndurbar square. O/nt. Hotel Grand.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 03:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KATHMANDU&nbsp; -&nbsp;\r\nPOKHARA</span><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">Drive via\r\nscenic view to Pokhara. Arrive Pokhara and check into hotel Barahi and rest. Evening\r\nif time permits visit Barahi temple and boating in Fewa Lake. O/nt. Hotel\r\nBarahi.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 04:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore POKHARA.</span><br></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\">Early morning drive to Sarangkot hill to view sunrise. Later\r\nhave breakfast at Sarangkot and spend time watching the gorgeous Mt. Fishtail &amp;\r\nMt. Annapurna range and optional program to enjoy para-gliding. Drive back to\r\nthe hotel, have lunch and rest for awhile, continue sightseeing visiting Bat-Cave,\r\nDevi’s fall &amp; Brindawasini Temple. O/nt. Hotel Barahi.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">Day05:&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; POKHARA\r\n– CHITWAN <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\">Drive after breakfast to Chitwan National Park for approx 4 –\r\n5 hours. On arrival meet the Jungle assistance and transfer to the Jungle camp.&nbsp; Welcome drinks and lunch will be served with a\r\nshort briefing about the “do and don’ts” of Jungle rules [including your jungle\r\nactivities schedule]. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:115%\">Afternoon go on Elephant safari penetrating the Jungle in\r\nsearch of various wildlife such as the great one-horned Rhino, Deer’s, bears, Crocodiles\r\nincluding the illusive Royal Bengal Tigers. Back in the camp in the evening\r\nlocal cultural dance and dinner .O/nt. Jungle lodge.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 06: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In CHITWAN</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">Full day Jungle\r\nactivities such as elephant safari, boating in Narayani river, jungle walk and\r\nelephant bathing. Overnight at jungle lodge.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 07:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CHITWAN - KATHMANDU&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">After\r\nbreakfast drive to back to Kathmandu, Transfer to Hotel and rest-of-the-day at</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">leisure for\r\nshopping. O/nt. at hotel.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Day 08:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; KATHMANDU&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%\">After\r\nbreakfast drive to airport for international departure.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 550, '<br>', '<br>', 'Yes', '2', 2, '8 days Pokhara Chitwan', '8 days Pokhara Chitwan', '2021-05-28 09:31:55', '2022-01-05 07:20:35');
