(10, 3, 'Mountain Biking in NEPAL (US$.620)', 'Mountain-Biking-in-NEPAL-(US$.620)', 'package-main-photo-10.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Can I bring my own bike?</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;color:#666666\">Bringing your own bike is the best way to\r\nensure you’ll have maximum comfort on your chosen tour. if bringing your own\r\nbike isn’t possible then we provide a hire bike. Bike hire prices vary with\r\nlocation and type of tour.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;color:#666666\">If you are bringing your own bike, most\r\nairlines have straightforward and affordable bike carriage policies and our\r\nstaff can offer plenty of advice on the various methods of packing and\r\ntravelling. We’ll even help you assemble it on arrival and pack it safe on way\r\nback!<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">What fitness levels do you\r\ncater for?</span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;color:#666666\">For all our destinations we cater for a\r\nwide variety of riders, from families embarking on a vehicle supported cultural\r\ncycle tour to the most adventurous of riders looking to ride the remotest and\r\nmost technical of trails, and everything in between.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;color:#666666\">If you have any apprehensions about\r\nwhether a tour or race will be too hard (or too easy), just get in contact and\r\nwe’ll talk you through it<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">How much luggage can I take\r\nwith me on tour?</span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"outline: 0px; text-size-adjust: 100%;\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt;color:#666666\">You are allowed to bring as much luggage\r\nas you want , but we request to limit the weight not to exceed 20kg’s per\r\nperson.</span><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'Mountain biking has become a hugely popular activity in Nepal largely because of the variety of terrain and the spectacular natural backdrop of mountains, rivers and forests. Rides range from flat, laid-back roads that wind through the tropical plains of the Terai region in the south of Nepal to more demanding trails in the Middle […]', '27.7172,85.3240', '2', 'APR OCT NOV', 'Adventurous', '23rd November 2022', '2021/10/01', '2021/10/10', '2021/10/08', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d210147.39707064038!2d-58.573384362124045!3d-34.61546111822767!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x95bcca3b4ef90cbd%3A0xa0b3812e88e88e87!2sBuenos+Aires%2C+Argentina!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sbd!4v1544189305968\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">DAY 1 Arrival in Kathmandu<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">You will be\r\nmet at Tribhuvan International airport by a representative and taken to the\r\nhotel which is located in the heart of the tourist district of Kathmandu,\r\nThamel (approximately a 20-minute drive).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 2<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Kathmandu to Pokhara<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Whilst you enjoy your breakfast, the luggage and bikes will be\r\nloaded onto the tour vehicle for the transfer to Pokhara (the bikes will\r\ncontinue to Jomsom ready for your arrival on Day 3).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">After breakfast you will be transferred to Kathmandu domestic\r\nairport for the 25-minute flight to the Lakeside town of Pokhara. OR\r\nalternatively you will be collected from your hotel for the approximate 8-hour\r\ntransfer via bus. This option will be chosen at the time of booking.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">On arrival in Pokhara, you will check into the hotel which will\r\nleave plenty of time in the afternoon and evening to stretch the legs and\r\nexplore the town.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 3<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Pokhara to Kagbeni via\r\nJomsom<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Biking\r\nDistance: 14km</span></i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">There are 2 options today!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Option 1:&nbsp;&nbsp;Following an early nutritious breakfast, a\r\nshort transfer will be made to Pokhara airport to catch a scenic morning flight\r\nto Jomsom, which takes approximately 20-minutes. The flight takes you above the\r\nPokhara valley and deep into the heart of the Himalayas. This is where you can\r\nget your first real glimpses of the mighty Himalaya mountain ranges, including\r\nthe breathtaking mountain views of Dhaulagiri and the Annapurna. Please bear in\r\nmind that these flights are weather dependent and can sometimes be delayed or\r\ncancelled at the last minute.&nbsp;Once you have landed in Jomsom, there will\r\nbe time to get kitted up and have a hot drink before the ensuing ride. The\r\nriding will be an easy 14km on mainly flat terrain to allow your body to adapt\r\nto the increase in altitude. The night’s accommodation will be at the beautiful\r\nTibetan village of Kagbeni.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Option 2: A nice and early start, and straight onto the jeep for\r\nthe 8-hour transfer to Kagbeni. You’ll start on sealed road, but this will soon\r\nturn into bumpy jeep-track and you’ll start to get a glimpse of what riding in\r\nthe Himalayas is all about! Imagine deep valley gorges, snow-capped mountains\r\n&amp; river passes. You will get to stop off for lunch and enjoy the\r\nspectacular scenery whilst taking in the stunning views around you, before\r\nfinally reaching your destination of the day – Kagbeni.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 4<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Kagbeni to Muktinath via\r\nJhong<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Biking\r\nDistance: 18km</span></i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Upon leaving Kagbeni, there will be an uphill ride to Muktinath\r\nwhich is at an elevation of 3900m.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">The route continues, by climbing the trail to the north side of\r\nthe gorge and on a dusty jeep track, which heads towards the mighty Thorong La\r\nPass via the village of Jhong. In Jhong, you can stop to catch your breath\r\nwhilst explore the ancient monastery and then have lunch basking in the\r\nsunshine whilst enjoying the stunning mountain views.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">The final section after lunch will be short and you should\r\narrive in Muktinath around mid-afternoon. You can spend this time to explore\r\nthe local village including monasteries and temples with your guide, or simply\r\nhave some time to rest.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 5<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Muktinath to Marpha<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Biking Distance:\r\n26km</span></i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">An early breakfast and start will be needed for Day 5, due to\r\nthe high winds in the valley that start to pick up around 11.00am. They can\r\nmake the ride very tough! The day starts with a slow ascent to Lupra Pass,\r\nwhere you will get to see the breathtaking views of Dhaulagiri and the\r\nAnnapurna ranges.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Once you get to the top of the pass, you will ride a fast\r\nstretch of downhill until you reach the river valley, from where there is a 6km\r\nflat section leading to Jomsom.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">After lunch in Jomsom, the trail undulates along the river until\r\nyou reach Marpha. For the more experienced and technical riders there are some\r\nalternative beautiful, fun and technical single-track options to take.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Marpha is famous for growing apples and making brandy and cider,\r\nso be sure to sample some local produce in the evening!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 6<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Marpha to Tatopani<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Biking\r\nDistance: 42km</span></i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">The trail from Marpha is mostly downhill to Tatopani. The trail\r\nstarts gentle and flat through pine forests and small villages, where you will\r\nfollow the river, and on a clear day, see stunning views of the snowcapped\r\npeaks. The lunch stop will be at the flowing waterfalls at Rukse Chaahara.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">With lunch finished, you will continue to ride fast-paced\r\ndownhill as the trail drops approximately 1000 meters on rough jeep track\r\nbefore you finally reach Tatopani. Tatopani is a cobbled street village, famous\r\nfor its rejuvenating hot springs at which you can enjoy a well-deserved soak to\r\nease any tired muscles.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 7<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Tatopani to Beni onwards to\r\nPokhara<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Biking\r\nDistance: 23km or 100km</span></i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Day 7 will be the final guided ride, taking you on jeep tracks\r\nwhich are predominantly flat but have a few ‘Nepali flat’ sections of up and\r\ndown to remind you that you are still in the Himalayas! The final destination\r\nis Beni where the guides will load the bikes up, and you will transfer by jeep\r\nback to Pokhara for a well-earned rest and perhaps a beer or 2!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">For those who want to continue the journey to Pokhara by bike,\r\nrather than the bumpy jeep ride, there is an option to ride all the way to\r\nPokhara from Tatopani, which will mean an extra 77km of riding.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 8<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Pokhara to Kathmandu\r\ntransfer<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">After breakfast you will return to Kathmandu via a 25-minute\r\nshort plane journey or 8 hours return on the bus.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Once back in Kathmandu, there will be time in the afternoon for\r\nsome trinket shopping or to explore some of the many temples and places of\r\ninterest in the city.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">Please let us know at the time of booking if you would prefer to\r\nstay in Pokhara a few extra days to check out some of the adventurous (or\r\nleisurely!) activities that it has to offer!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:#666666\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 9<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\">Departure<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Transfer to\r\nthe airport or continue with additional itinerary.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;color:#666666\">Let us know\r\nif you would like to see the full list of activities that we have to offer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 620, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#595959;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;\r\npadding:0in\">Privacy policy</span><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#29293A\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#595959;\r\nborder:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">Any\r\npersonal information that we collect about you may be used for any purpose\r\nassociated with the operation of a Trip or to send you marketing material in\r\nrelation to our events and special offers. We will otherwise treat your details\r\nin accordance with our privacy policy (available for viewing on our Website).</span><span style=\"font-size:5.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#595959;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;\r\npadding:0in\">1. Age &amp; Health requirements</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n13.5pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#29293A\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#595959;\r\nborder:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">Minimum\r\nGeneral Policy: For the majority of our trips the minimum age is 15 at the time\r\nof travel. All travelers under the age of 18 must be accompanied by a legal\r\nguardian, or in lieu of a legal guardian, by an escort over the age of 18,\r\nappointed by their legal guardian. The legal guardian or their designee will be\r\nresponsible for the traveler under the age of 18 days to daycare. If a legal\r\nguardian elects to designate an escort in their lieu, they will be required to\r\ncomplete and sign a relevant document, to delegate their authority.</span><span style=\"font-size:5.0pt;font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#595959;\r\nborder:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">Maximum\r\nGen