(12, 10, 'Pilgrimage Tour Nepal (US$.1200)', 'Pilgrimage-Tour-Nepal-(US$.1200)', 'package-main-photo-6164ed8b11d4a.jpg', '<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f38b4189-7fff-0673-3fcb-028e58ac1755\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\">How can I obtain a visa\r\nto travel to Nepal? Is there any country or embassy that issues visas on behalf\r\nof Nepal?</span></b><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\"><br>\r\nThe best way to apply for visa is from the Nepalese diplomatic missions in your\r\ncountry. The other choice is to get it from Immigration office at the entry\r\npoints of Nepal. All foreign nationals, except Indian Citizens need visas to\r\nenter Nepal. TIA Airport upon the payment of the fee of US$ 40.Two copies of\r\npassport photos are required on the arrival. The visas can be extended, if\r\nrequired, upon the additional payment of US$ 30.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>When is the best season to travel to Nepal?</b><br>\r\nThe best season to visit Nepal is from March to May and September to November.\r\nHowever, some tourists prefer to visit Nepal in the lean season too because\r\nthere are abundant choices in terms of accommodation and flight bookings can be\r\ndone very easily. June/August it is better to do trek belong to rain shadow\r\nlike Upper Mustang, Dolpa in Nepal and Mt. Kailash in Tibet.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Do we need to cover travel insurance?</b><br>\r\nYes, we advise you to get your insurance cover from your respective country.<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<b>Do I have to tip my guide?</b><br>\r\nYour porter/guide should not \'ask you\' for anything, however at the end of your\r\ntrek if he has done a good job and you feel he warrants a thank you, by all\r\nmeans give him something.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\">Are there any age\r\nrestrictions?</span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:8.0pt\">\r\nNo, there are any age restrictions. We can be designed trek for\r\nchildren/teenager/ pensioner. For children and pensioner, we offer short and\r\neasy tours around Kathmandu and Pokhara Valley. For adult and teenager. <br>\r\n<!--[if !supportLineBreakNewLine]--><br>\r\n<!--[endif]--><o:p></o:p></span></p>', 'On the 18th of May, 2006, Nepal became a secular state. Prior to this decision by Nepal’s democratically elected House of Representatives, Nepal was the last Hindu Kingdom on earth, the monarch widely regarded as a living incarnation of Vishnu. Today, approximately 80% of the population of Nepal is Hindu. Other folks, Sherpa, Tamang, Newar […]', '27.7172,85.3240', '2', 'APR OCT NOV', 'RELIGIOUS', '23rd November 2022', '2021/10/01', '2021/10/11', '2021/10/08', NULL, '<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f38b4189-7fff-0673-3fcb-028e58ac1755\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Arrival in Kathmandu<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kathmandu tour (Pashupatinath, Boudhanath\r\n&amp; Budhanilkantha)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenic drive to Namo-Buddha &amp; explore\r\nPanauti 2-3 hrs 1,750 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day\r\n4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenic drive to Manakamana &amp; drive to Pokhara 6-7 hrs 827 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Visit Talbarahi (Island Temple) &amp; drive\r\nto Tatopani 5-6 hrs 1,190 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenic drive to Muktinath via Jomsom 8-9\r\nhrs 3,800 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Explore Muktinath &amp; drive to Marpha 5-6\r\nhrs 2,650 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 8&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenic drive to Pokhara via Kalika Temple of\r\nKusma 5-6 hrs 827 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 9&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scenic drive to Lumbini via Palpa 7-8\r\nhrs 150 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 10&nbsp;&nbsp; Full-day Lumbini sightseeing 150 m<o:p></o:p></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 7.5pt;\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Day 11&nbsp;&nbsp; Fly\r\nback to Kathmandu &amp; report to international airport or exit from Indian\r\nborder<o:p></o:p></span></p>', 1200, '<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-f38b4189-7fff-0673-3fcb-028e58ac1755\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#59595