(16, 4, '7 Days Darjeeling Sikkim Tour (US$.570)', '7-Days-Darjeeling-Sikkim-Tour-(US$.570)', 'package-main-photo-61647b4f6bd1c.jpg', '<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-17200f63-7fff-ac14-a0a9-f4cfe9f7dc43\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Darjeeling comes from the Tibetan “Dorje Ling” meaning the place of the Thunderbolt and sits on the border with Tibet in West Bengal, India. This area is intertwined with the history of Nepal, it used to be Nepal after an 18th century invasion but the British took it back, and as a result is also […]</span></span><br></p>', 'Darjeeling comes from the Tibetan “Dorje Ling” meaning the place of the Thunderbolt and sits on the border with Tibet in West Bengal, India. This area is intertwined with the history of Nepal, it used to be Nepal after an 18th century invasion but the British took it back, and as a result is also […]', '27.0410,88.2663', '3', 'April to December', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/10/02', '2021/10/11', '2021/10/02', 'nn', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, &quot;serif&quot;;\">Day 01</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Arrive in Bagdogra airport and meet our\r\nassistance and transfer to Darjeeling, check in to hotel Villa Everest or\r\nGolden Height or similar &amp; rest.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Day 02<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Transfer to Tiger Hill (2550 m), to\r\nsee the sunrise over Kanchenjunga then - visit Ghum Monastery Sightseeing\r\nDarjeeling: Japanese Temple, Pagoda of the world, the Himalayan Zoo Padmadzhi\r\nNaidu Himalayan Mountain Institute and Tenzing Norgay, Tenzing rock and Gomba,\r\nthe Tibetan Centre and tea plantations. Overnight at hotel Villa Everest or\r\nGolden Height or </span>similar.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Day 03<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:\r\njustify;line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">In the morning, after breakfast,\r\ntransfer to Pelling (Pemayangtse), On arrival, check in to hotel and rest. Then\r\nvisit the Pemayangtse Monastery. Overnight at </span>Golden Height / De regency /\r\n