(28, 4, 'Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh and Hurghada and the pyramids - Tour', 'Cairo-Nile-River-Sharm-El-Sheikh-Hurghada-and-Pyramids-Tour', 'package-main-photo-61793796b9e1b.jpg', '<p><b>Program includes:</b></p><p>Meet and greet service by our representatives at airports.</p><p>Assistance of our guest relations during your stay.</p><p>All transfers by a private air-conditioned vehicle.</p><p>Transfer from Luxor to Hurghada by private air-conditioned vehicle.</p><p>Domestic flight from Cairo to Aswan.</p><p>Accommodation for 4 nights in Cairo including bed &amp; breakfast.</p><p>Accommodation for 1 night in Aswan including bed &amp; breakfast.</p><p>Accommodation for 3 nights on a 5-star superior cruise on full board.</p><p>Accommodation for 3 nights in Hurghada including&nbsp; daily breakfast.</p><p>English speaking&nbsp; Egyptologist tour guide.</p><p>All sightseeing tours on the cruise sharing Jordan Tours group.</p><p>All sightseeing tours in Cairo, Luxor, Aswan as mentioned in the itinerary.</p><p>All sightseeing tours in Cairo are private tours.</p><p>Entrance fees to all sites as indicated on the itinerary.</p><p>Lunch during your trip in Cairo Meals as mention in the above itinerary.</p><p>Bottled water during the trips portage when needed.</p><p>All service charges and taxes.</p><p>30 minutes of local calling (5 minutes international) and a mobile phone loaned for the length of your stay or an Egyptian sim card for your unlocked mobile device.</p><p><br></p><p><b>Program excludes:</b></p><p>International Airfare</p><p>Entry visa to Egypt</p><p>Any optional tours</p><p>Personal expenditures such as drinks during meals, laundry, phone call…..etc</p><p>Entrance&nbsp; fees inside the Great Pyramid of Cheops, Mummies room at the Museum or inside Tutankhamen Tomb at Valley of the Kings</p><p>Tipping</p>', 'Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh, Hurghada and the pyramids-Tour', 'Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh, Hurghada and the pyramids- Tour', '2', 'April to December', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/11/01', '2021/11/23', '2021/11/01', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2570.2293101616856!2d-97.14080388428864!3d49.89449807940243!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x52ea715b011f23fd%3A0x3f1400ee9c469396!2s360%20Main%20St%2030th%20Floor%2C%20Winnipeg%2C%20MB%20R3C%204G1%2C%20Canada!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1634104210730!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', '<p>Schedule:</p><p>Every Saturday, Monday, Thursday</p><p>Type:</p><p>Private Tour in Cairo &amp; group Tour on the Cruise</p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">DAY 1: ARRIVAL CAIRO</span><br></p><p>Welcome to land of the Pharaoh’s, welcome to Cairo, Egypt</p><p>Your tour manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International Airport and then will escort you to the hotel by an exclusive air-conditioned, deluxe vehicle. At the hotel, the tour manager will assist with a smooth check-in, review your holiday itinerary with you and confirm pick-up times for each tour. Overnight in Cairo. Welcome Drinks.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 2: PYRAMIDS / SAKKARA</p><p>After breakfast, you will be accompanied by your personal guide to Giza Plateau to visit the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren, and Mykerinus&nbsp; – Famous Sphinx and Valley temple facing the great statue; an additional visit to the Solar Boat in front of Cheops Pyramid (extra ticket on spot). Lunch will be served at a local, favorite restaurant, then you’ll proceed to the Sakkara area to visit Sakkara Complex and first pyramid ever built (Djoser Pyramid).</p><p>Move to Memphis;&nbsp; Old kingdom’s&nbsp; capital and famous Necropolis.</p><p>Overnight in Cairo.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 3: CAIRO SIGHTSEEING</p><p>After breakfast at your hotel in Cairo and then you will be escorted by your private guide to visit: Egyptian&nbsp; Museum, Treasures room for the child king Tutankhamen, alongside many other fascinating artifacts, an additional visit to the mummies room at the museum (extra ticket purchased there), lunch during the tour at local restaurant, then a visit to the Saladin Citadel including the&nbsp; Mohamed Ali Alabaster&nbsp; Mosque inside. Continue to Coptic Cairo to visit the Hanging Church and Ben Ezra Synagogue, a drive to Islamic Cairo, where you will be able to explore Khan El Khalili,&nbsp; Cairo’s oldest bazaar.</p><p>Overnight in Cairo.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 4: FLIGHT FROM CAIRO TO ASWAN</p><p>Breakfast,&nbsp; then transfer to Cairo Airport for a flight to Aswan. Optional Tour (not included)&nbsp; to enjoy one of Egypt’s top tourist attractions, Abu Simbel temple, which was originally carved out of the mountainside during the reign of Pharaoh Ramesses&nbsp; II approximately in the 13th century BC, as a lasting monument to himself and his queen Nefertari.</p><p>Overnight in Aswan.</p><p>Note: In case you would like to do Abu Simbel Tour, so you will do it on day 05 and Aswan sightseeing tours will be on day 4.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 5 : ASWAN SIGHTSEEING</p><p>Breakfast at your hotel in Aswan. Then transfer to embark your Nile River Cruise before Lunch, then enjoy visiting the world famous High Dam, the awesome Philae temple, which is devoted to the two goddesses Isis and Hathor, and the largest known ancient obelisk,&nbsp; located in the northern region of the stone quarries of ancient Egypt, the Unfinished&nbsp; Obelisk.</p><p>Dinner on board and overnight in Aswan.</p><p>Meals:&nbsp; Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 6: KOM OMBO / EDFU</p><p>Sail to KomOmbo, have breakfast&nbsp; on board and Visit the Temple shared by two gods Sobek and Haeroris in KomOmbo. Sail to Edfu, lunch on board after that Visit the best-preserved cult temple in Egypt, Horus Temple in Edfu. Take afternoon tea during sailing to Esna.</p><p>Dinner and overnight on board.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 7: LUXOR WEST BANK</p><p>Sail to Luxor, have breakfast&nbsp; on board then Visit the West Bank,&nbsp; take an excursion&nbsp; to the royal cemetery&nbsp; of 62 Pharaohs,&nbsp; Valley of the Kings, then to the mortuary&nbsp; Temple of Queen Hatshepsut, which was built by the architects&nbsp; of the New Kingdom Pharaoh Hatshepsut&nbsp; approximately in the 15th century BC, at El-Deir El-Bahari&nbsp; and the Colossi of Memnon. Lunch on board. Enjoy afternoon tea during sailing.</p><p>Dinner on board Overnight in Luxor.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 8: LUXOR EAST BANK / HURGHADA</p><p>Breakfast on board, disembark from your Nile cruise after breakfast then transfer to visit Karnak and Luxor temples.&nbsp; In the afternoon transfer to Hurghada on the Red Sea. From Luxor to Hurghada is about a 3.5-hour drive.</p><p>Overnight in Hurghada.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 9: HURGHADA VACATION</p><p>Optional tours are available to experience the exquisite diving and snorkeling among the Red Sea coral reefs to see many exotic and beautiful species of fish. Or choose one of the many other activities&nbsp; such as windsurfing, sailing and deep-sea fishing.</p><p>Overnight&nbsp; in Hurghada.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 10: HURGHADA VACATION</p><p>Optional tours are available to experience the exquisite diving and snorkeling among the Red Sea coral reefs and see some amazing rare fish. Or choose one of the many other activities such as windsurfing, sailing and deep-sea fishing.</p><p>Overnight in Hurghada.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 11: BACK TO CAIRO FROM HURGHADA BY FLIGHT.</p><p>Breakfast at your hotel in Hurghada with time for leisure and then a transfer to Hurghada&nbsp; Airport for a flight to Cairo.</p><p>Overnight&nbsp; in Cairo.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 12: CAIRO - FLY BACK HOME</p><p>Breakfast at the hotel in Cairo – leisure time before your flight – check out and then travel to Cairo International Airport for final departure.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p>', 2, '<p>&nbsp;Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh ,Hurghada and Pyramids&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">- Tour</span></p>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">&nbsp;Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh ,Hurghada and Pyramids&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">- Tour</span><br></p>', 'Yes', '11', 9, 'Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh, Hurghada and Pyramids - Tour', 'Cairo, Nile River, Sharm El Sheikh, Hurghada and Pyramids - Tour', '2021-10-27 11:27:18', '2021-12-06 12:06:29'),
(29, 11, 'Cairo, Nile & Sharm', 'cairo-nile-sharm', 'package-main-photo-617939764e609.jpg', '<p><b>Program includes:</b></p><p>Meet and greet service by our representatives at airports</p><p>Assistance of our guest relations during your stay.</p><p>All transfers by a private air-conditioned vehicle</p><p>Domestic flight (Cairo/Aswan- Luxor/ Sharm – Sharm / Cairo)</p><p>Accommodation for 4 nights in Cairo including bed and breakfast</p><p>Accommodation for 3 nights on a 5 star superior cruise on full board</p><p>Accommodation for 4 nights in Sharm El Sheikh including bed &amp; breakfast</p><p>All sightseeing tours in Cairo (Private Guided Tours)</p><p>All sightseeing tours on the cruise sharing Jordan Tours group</p><p>Entrance fees to all sites as indicated on the itinerary</p><p>Bottled water during your tour Meals at hotels, Nile Cruise and during tours as mentioned in the itinerary</p><p>Portage when needed</p><p>30 minutes of local calling (5 minutes international) and a mobile phone loaned for the length of your stay or an Egyptian sim card for your unlocked mobile device.</p><p>All service charges and taxes</p><p><br></p><p><b>Program excludes:</b></p><p>International Airfare</p><p>Entry visa to Egypt</p><p>Any optional tours</p><p>Personal expenses such as drinks during meals, laundry, phone calls…..etc</p><p>Entrance&nbsp; fees inside the Great Pyramid of Cheops, Mummies room at the Museum or inside Tutankhamen Tomb at Valley of the Kings</p><p>Tipping</p>', 'Cairo, Nile & Sharm', 'Cairo, Nile & Sharm', '2', 'April to November', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/11/09', '2021/11/29', '2021/11/01', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2570.2293101616856!2d-97.14080388428864!3d49.89449807940243!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x52ea715b011f23fd%3A0x3f1400ee9c469396!2s360%20Main%20St%2030th%20Floor%2C%20Winnipeg%2C%20MB%20R3C%204G1%2C%20Canada!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1634104210730!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', '<p>Schedule:</p><p>Every Saturday, wednesday, Thursday</p><p>Type:</p><p>Private tour in Cairo &amp; group tour on the cruise.</p><p>DAY 1: ARRIVAL CAIRO</p><p>Welcome to land of the Pharaoh’s, welcome to Cairo, Egypt</p><p>Your tour manager will meet and assist you at Cairo International Airport and then will escort you to the hotel by an exclusive air-conditioned, deluxe vehicle. At the hotel, the tour manager will assist with a smooth check-in, review your holiday itinerary with you and confirm pick-up times for each tour.</p><p>Overnight in Cairo.</p><p>DAY 2: PYRAMIDS / SAKKARA</p><p>After breakfast, you will be accompanied by your personal guide to Giza Plateau to visit the Great Pyramids of Cheops, Chefren, and Mykerinus&nbsp; – Famous Sphinx and Valley temple facing the great statue; an additional visit to the Solar Boat in front of Cheops Pyramid (extra ticket on spot). Lunch will be served at a local, favorite restaurant, then you’ll proceed to the Sakkara area to visit Sakkara Complex and first pyramid ever built (Djoser Pyramid).</p><p>Move to Memphis;&nbsp; Old kingdom’s&nbsp; capital and famous Necropolis.</p><p>Overnight&nbsp; in Cairo.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch</p><p>DAY 3: FLIGHT FROM CAIRO TO ASWAN - ASWAN SIGHTSEEING.</p><p>After breakfast, you’ll&nbsp; transfer to Cairo Airport for a flight to Aswan. Memphis Tours representative will meet you at Aswan Airport.&nbsp; Then you will be transferred by a private A/C vehicle to your Nile Cruise ship for embarkation from Aswan before lunch. Enjoy visiting the world famous High Dam and the Temple of Philae on Isis Island, the Granite Quarries and the Unfinished Obelisk.</p><p>Dinner on board and overnight in Aswan.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>DAY 4: KOM OMBO / EDFU</p><p>Sail to KomOmbo, have breakfast onboard and Visit the Temple shared by two gods Sobek and Haeroris in KomOmbo. Sail to Edfu, lunch on board after that Visit the best-preserved cult temple in Egypt, Horus Temple in Edfu. Take afternoon tea during sailing to Esna.</p><p>Dinner and overnight on board.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>DAY 5: LUXOR SIGHTSEEING.</p><p>Have your breakfast onboard, during your sail to Luxor, then visit the West Bank and the Valley of the Kings, The Temple of Queen Hatshepsut at El-Deir El-Bahari&nbsp; &amp; the Colossi of Memnon. Lunch onboard, then proceed to visit East Bank (Karnak &amp; Luxor Temples).&nbsp; Enjoy afternoon tea during sailing.</p><p>Have your dinner on board and overnight in Luxor.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch, Dinner</p><p>DAY 6: LUXOR/ FLY TO SHARM</p><p>Breakfast on board, disembark from your Nile cruise after breakfast, and then you will be transferred to Luxor Airport for a flight to Sharm.</p><p>Upon arrival at Sharm Airport,&nbsp; you’ll travel to your hotel in Sharm and stay overnight.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast.</p><p>Note: Most flights from Luxor to Sharm are indirect flights via Cairo Airport.<span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p>DAY 7: SHARM EL SHIEKH.</p><p>Free day in Sharm or join our optional tour to Ras Mohammed&nbsp; National Park which is both a terrestrial and an aquatic nature reserve.&nbsp; The 480 square kilometer protected area lies where the Gulf of Suez meets the Gulf of Aqaba in Sinai’s southern extremity.&nbsp; The arid desert terrain of sand dunes, gravel plains, fossilized corals and granite mountains is home to a number of rare mammal species: the Dorcas gazelles, Nubian ibex and red foxes. Easier to spot are the local birds: like terns, herons, gulls and ospreys.&nbsp; Thousands of white storks pass through Ras Mohammed each year, heading south during September/October and back north during April/May.&nbsp; About 85 flora species live in the park, including mangroves. Overnight in Sharm.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>DAY 8: SHARM EL SHIEKH.</p><p>Free day in Sharm or join our optional tour to one of the natural wonders of the Sinai, the Colored Canyon is majestic.&nbsp; Take a walk among dramatic sandstone&nbsp; canyon walls streaked with melting yellows, purples,&nbsp; reds, magenta and gold. In certain places, the canyon walls reach up to 40 meters. You feel as if you are enclosed in a spectacular coloring book.</p><p>Overnight in Sharm.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>DAY 9: SHARM EL SHIEKH.</p><p>Free day in Sharm or join our optional tour to The Monastery of St. Catherine located at the heart of Sinai and at the foot of the Gebel Musa, or Mount Moses. Fronted by gardens and cypress trees, the monastery is owned and run by the Greek Orthodox&nbsp; Church. Its rich library houses the world’s second largest collection of illuminated manuscripts after the Vatican.&nbsp; You can see the Burning Bush and a large number of antique works of art: invaluable icons, beautifully carved doors, exquisite wall paintings and other fine religious ornaments.</p><p>Overnight in Sharm.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>DAY 10: BACK TO CAIRO FROM SHARM BY FLIGHT.</p><p>Breakfast at your hotel in Sharm El Sheikh and then you will be transferred to Sharm El Sheikh Airport for a flight to Cairo.</p><p>Overnight in Cairo.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p><p>DAY 11 : CAIRO SIGHTSEEING.</p><p>Start your day by visiting the Egyptian&nbsp; Museum, where you will admire the splendid collection&nbsp; of Tutankhamun alongside many other fascinating artifacts.&nbsp; Transfer to the Salah El Din Citadel which was constructed by Salah El Din in 1183 AD to defend Cairo from the armies of Crusaders. After that visit Mohamed Ali Alabaster&nbsp; Mosque which was designed by the architect&nbsp; Yousif Boushnaq, a Turkish man who came from Istanbul especially to build this great mosque for Mohamed Ali, the ruler of Egypt (1805-1849) who ruled for over 45 years. Lunch will be served in a local restaurant. Then proceed to explore Khan El Khalili Bazaar, Cairo’s old bazaar. Then we move on to Coptic Cairo to visit the Hanging Church, Ben Ezra Synagogue, Church of St. Barbara, Church of Abu Serga.</p><p>Back to hotel and overnight in Cairo</p><p>Meals: Breakfast,&nbsp; Lunch</p><p>DAY 12: CAIRO - FLY BACK HOME</p><p>Breakfast at the hotel in Cairo – leisure time before your flight – check out and then transfer to Cairo International Airport for final departure.</p><p>Meals: Breakfast</p>', 30, '<p>Cairo, Nile &amp; Sharm<br></p>', '<p>Cairo, Nile &amp; Sharm<br></p>', 'No', '11', 1, 'Cairo, Nile & Sharm', 'Cairo, Nile & Sharm', '2021-10-27 11:35:18', '2021-12-10 01:02:17'),
(30, 3, '4 Days Dubai Break', '4-days-dubai-break', 'package-main-photo-618798997c84f.jpg', '<p><b>Program includes:</b></p><p>3 nights accommodation</p><p>Daily breakfast</p><p>Meet &amp; Assist</p><p>Private transfers (Airport – Hotel – Airport)</p><p>Classic Dubai city tour</p><p>Desert safari &amp; BB dinner</p><p>Entrance fees and taxes</p><p><b>Program excludes</b><br></p><p>Visa Fees – charges 85 USD</p><p>Any item of personal nature</p><p>Meals not mentioned in the itinerary</p><p>Beverages unless stated otherwise</p><p>Tips and porterage.</p><p>Dirham Fee</p>', 'Dubai is a city known for luxury shopping, ultramodern architecture and a lively nightlife scene. BURJ KHALIFA 830 meters-tall tower, a dominating skyscraper-filled skyline and the base has Water Fountain with jets & lights choreographed to music. \r\nArtificial islands offshore, The Palm, a resort with water and marine-animal park, tree-shaped Palm Jumeirah island is known for glitzy hotels, posh apartment towers and upmarket global restaurants.\r\nBURJ AL ARAB Jumeirah is designed like a billowing sail standing height of 321 m. One of the most consistently voted the world’s most luxurious hotel, round-the-clock private butlers and unique transfers of Rolls-Royce fleet with private beach. It has 199 luxury suites range from 170 to 780 square meters having rain shower also a Jacuzzi in every suite, it also has a range of award winning restaurants, conference hall with magnificent banqueting venues.', 'Dubai Break', '2', 'April to December', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/11/01', '2021/11/29', '2021/11/01', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2570.2293101616856!2d-97.14080388428864!3d49.89449807940243!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x52ea715b011f23fd%3A0x3f1400ee9c469396!2s360%20Main%20St%2030th%20Floor%2C%20Winnipeg%2C%20MB%20R3C%204G1%2C%20Canada!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1634104210730!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', '<p>DAY 1: ARRIVAL</p><p>Meet &amp; assist at the Dubai International Airport followed by transfer to your hotel.</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 2: CLASSIC DUBAI CITY TOUR</p><p>(Mon/Wed/Sat)- Half day guided tour on sharing basis.</p><p>Enjoy the magnificent view of Dubai Creek while driving through the heritage area of Bastakiya, with its fascinating old Wind Towered Houses built by wealthy merchants. We will visit the 180-year-old Al Fahidi Fort, which today houses the Dubai Museum. We continue our journey by Abra, a traditional water taxi across the creek and stroll through the spice and gold souks or markets. On our way to Burj Al Arab, one of Dubai’s landmarks, we make a photo stop at the Jumeirah Mosque.</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 3: AFTERNOON DESERT SAFARI &amp; BBQ DINNER</p><p>Enjoy your morning at leisure. Safari tour with English speaking driver on sharing basis .</p><p>In the afternoon, our safari guides will take you in a 4-wheel drive into the golden sand dunes of Arabia. Experience the thrill of a lifetime while riding through the dunes. Enjoy a beautiful scenic sunset overlooking the desert. Then continue to our Bedouin campsite, where you can enjoy camel riding, Henna design, Arabic gava, local dresses, soft drinks, tea or coffee, a water pipe and a delicious barbeque buffet. Adding to the atmosphere of the night is an enchanting belly dancer performing to the Arabic rhythms.</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 4: DEPARTURE</p><p>Check out before noon and transfer to Dubai International Airport.</p><p><br></p><p>Optional: Marina Dhow Cruise</p><p>USD 80/person – Two hours Marina Dhow Cruise on sharing basis.</p><p>A Dhow Cruise Dinner in Dubai has been a classic for many years running, however, traditionally it has been done in The Creek. A new concept emerged with the building of a luxurious and stylish area – Dubai Marina. The old concept of the Dhow Cruise has been reinvented and remodeled to fit the Dubai Marina atmosphere and has quickly become a new classic.</p><p>One of the things that make the Dinner Cruise in Dubai Marina special is the views of the new Dubai Area that are absolutely stunning at night. Dubai Marina is a vibrant area with lots of coffee shops, restaurants, boutiques and people enjoying themselves.</p><p>The traditional wooden dhow that has been used for decades as a primary shipping vessel is a great contrast to the ultra-modern, and almost futuristic views of Dubai Marina, providing a balance between new and old.</p><p><br></p>', 85, '<p>Dubai Break<br></p>', '<p>Dubai Break<br></p>', 'Yes', '12', 9, 'Dubai Break', 'Dubai Break', '2021-10-27 11:44:06', '2021-11-07 09:12:57'),
