(32, 2, '3 Days Dubai Stop Over', '3-days-dubai-stop-over', 'package-main-photo-61879af02210b.jpg', '<p><b>Program includes:</b></p><p>1 night accommodation</p><p>Daily breakfast</p><p>Meet &amp; Assist</p><p>Private transfers (Airport – Hotel – Airport)</p><p>Classical Dubai Tour.</p><p>Entrance fees and taxes</p><p><br></p><p><b>Program excludes</b></p><p>Visa Fees – charges 85 USD</p><p>Any item of personal nature</p><p>Meals not mentioned in the itinerary</p><p>Beverages unless stated otherwise</p><p>Tips and porterage.</p><p>Dirham Fee</p><p>Optional tours</p>', 'Dubai is a city known for luxury shopping, ultramodern architecture and a lively nightlife scene. BURJ KHALIFA 830 meters-tall tower, a dominating skyscraper-filled skyline and the base has Water Fountain with jets & lights choreographed to music.', 'Dubai Stop Over (3 days)', '2', 'April to December', 'Easy', '23rd November 2022', '2021/11/01', '2021/11/19', '2021/11/03', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2570.2293101616856!2d-97.14080388428864!3d49.89449807940243!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x52ea715b011f23fd%3A0x3f1400ee9c469396!2s360%20Main%20St%2030th%20Floor%2C%20Winnipeg%2C%20MB%20R3C%204G1%2C%20Canada!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1634104210730!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', '<p><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">DAY 1: ARRIVAL</span><br></p><p>Meet at the Dubai International Airport followed by transfer to your hotel.</p><p>Optional: Afternoon Desert Safari &amp; BBQ dinner</p><p>USD 70/person (daily) – Safari tour with English driver on sharing basis.</p><p>In the afternoon, our safari guides will take you in a 4-wheel drive into the golden sand dunes of Arabia. Experience the thrill of a lifetime while riding through the dunes. Enjoy a beautiful scenic sunset overlooking the desert. Then continue to our Bedouin campsite, where you can enjoy camel riding, Henna design, Arabic gava, local dresses, soft drinks, tea or coffee, a&nbsp; Hubbly Bubbly and a delicious barbeque buffet. Adding to the atmosphere of the night is an enchanting belly dancer performing to the Arabic rhythms.</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 2: CLASSIC DUBAI CITY TOUR</p><p>(Mon/Wed/Sat)- Half day guided tour on sharing basis.</p><p>Enjoy the magnificent view of Dubai Creek while driving through the heritage area of Bastakiya, with its fascinating old Wind Towered Houses built by wealthy merchants. We will visit the 180-year-old Al Fahidi Fort, which today houses the Dubai Museum. We continue our journey by Abra, a traditional water taxi across the creek and stroll through the spice and gold souks or markets. On our way to Burj Al Arab, one of Dubai’s landmarks, we make a photo stop at the Jumeirah Mosque.</p><p><br></p><p>DAY 3: DEPARTURE</p><p>Check out before noon and transfer to Dubai International Airport.</p><p>Optional: Marina Dhow Cruise</p><p>USD 80/person – Two hours Marina Dhow Cruise on sharing basis.</p><p>A Dhow Cruise Dinner in Dubai has been a classic for many years running, however, traditionally it has been done in The Creek. A new concept emerged with the building of a luxurious and stylish area – Dubai Marina. The old concept of the Dhow Cruise has been reinvented and remodeled to fit the Dubai Marina atmosphere and has quickly become a new classic.</p><p>One of the things that make the Dinner Cruise in Dubai Marina special is the views of the new Dubai Area that are absolutely stunning at night. Dubai Marina is a vibrant area with lots of coffee shops, restaurants, boutiques and people enjoying themselves.</p><p>The traditional wooden dhow that has been used for decades as a primary shipping vessel is a great contrast to the ultra-modern, and almost futuristic views of Dubai Marina, providing a balance between new and old.</p>', 85, '<p>Dubai Stop Over (3 days)<br></p>', '<p>Dubai Stop Over (3 days)<br></p>', 'Yes', '12', 2, 'Dubai Stop Over (3 days)', 'Dubai Stop Over (3 days)', '2021-10-27 11:53:00', '2021-12-12 13:05:03'),
(33, 1, '2 Days Jerusalem Bethlehem', '2-days-jerusalem-bethlehem', 'package-main-photo-6187a04a3c345.jpg', '<p><b>Program includes:</b></p><p>&nbsp;Entrance fees to the mentioned sites in the program.</p><p>1 nights’ accommodation includes bed and breakfast sharing twin or triple standard room. (Single supplement applies if you want a single room).</p><p>Transport by experienced English speaking driver in air-conditioned vehicle.</p><p>Government Licensed malty speaking tour guide in Jerusalem.</p><p>1 small mineral water per person per day.</p><p><b>Program excludes:</b></p><p>All lunches and dinner (please see meals supplement below).</p><p>All drinks.</p><p>Any services not mentioned in the program.</p><p>Tips for driver, guide and hotel staff.</p><p>Exit tax out of Palestine/ Israel: NIS 182 pp (approx. $52 pp – subject to Change).</p><p>Transfers between the Israeli terminal and the Jordanian terminal. Cost of shuttle bus is&nbsp; ($10) plus ($2) per piece of luggage each way.</p><p>Israel visa for nationality required that.</p>', 'Jerusalem – the Holy land – Hub of Spirituality and Divinity\r\nThe Old City of Jerusalem is the prime attraction where you’ll see a number of ancient sites with religious significance and importance. There, are the pools of Belt Hasda – where Jesus held the crippled man and then Dolorosa – way of grief – traditionally accepted as the last route trodden by Jesus. Don’t miss the 14 Stations of the Cross to Golgotha – where Jesus was crucified marking important events along the route. Pilate’s Judgment Hall, the Chapel of the Flagellation where Roman soldiers flogged Jesus and placed a crown of thorns on his head, the Ecce Homo Arch and the convent of the Sisters of Zion, are some other destinations to see during your tour to Jerusalem – the holy land. Your trip to holy land would be incomplete without visiting these destinations.', 'Jerusalem Bethlehem', '2', 'April to December', '3', '23rd November 2022', '2021/11/01', '2021/11/29', '2021/11/01', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2570.2293101616856!2d-97.14080388428864!3d49.89449807940243!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x52ea715b011f23fd%3A0x3f1400ee9c469396!2s360%20Main%20St%2030th%20Floor%2C%20Winnipeg%2C%20MB%20R3C%204G1%2C%20Canada!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1634104210730!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe>', '<p>DAY 1: ALLENBY – MT. OF OLIVE – JERUSALEMMOLD CITY</p><p>Arrival from Allenby border and transfer to Jerusalem</p><p>Drive to the Mount of Olives for a wonderful view of Jerusalem. Then go to the Peter Noster with the Lord’s Prayer in different languages.</p><p>From the Mount of Olives the traditional Palm Sunday route takes you to the foot of the hill and sees the Garden of Gethsemane with its ancient olive trees.</p><p>Enter the Old City through the Dung gate to visit the Wailing (or western) Wall and view the Haram Al Sharif with the Al-Aqsa Mosque and the Dome of the Rock.</p><p>Walk the Via Dolorosa with its Stations of the Cross till you arrive at the Church of the Holy Sepulcher, where Jesus was crucified and buried, and then rose again.</p><p>Leave the city through the bazaars to the west by Jaffa Gate.</p><p>Drive through West Jerusalem to see the various landmarks.</p><p>Overnight in Jerusalem</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>DAY 2: JERUSALEM – BETHLEHEM – SHEPERDSFIELD - ALLENBY</p>', 200, '<p>Jerusalem Bethlehem<br></p>', '<p>Jerusalem Bethlehem<br></p>', 'No', '13', 6, 'Jerusalem Bethlehem', 'Jerusalem Bethlehem', '2021-10-28 06:45:03', '2021-11-07 11:08:06'),
