(83, 3, '10 Days Wonders of CANADA ($.3500)', '10-Days-wonders-of-CANADA', 'package-main-photo-61bacd044c4d6.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span class=\"bold\"><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nborder:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">Which are the top Canadian cities to visit?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">Looking\r\nfor&nbsp;Canada packages&nbsp;and cannot settle for the places to visit? You\r\nshould zero in on these cities to make the most of the second largest country\r\nin the world; Montreal, Quebec City, Vancouver, Ontario, Calgary, Toronto, and\r\nVictoria.</span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span style=\"border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">Which is the best time to visit Canada?</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></span></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">If you\r\nare in the process of short listing Canada tour packages, make sure you know\r\nits seasons well in order to plan the month of your visit. The peak season,\r\nhowever, are the summer months starting from late June to all of September when\r\nthe air is nice and warm and the schools out of session. Canada’s most popular\r\ndestinations like Montreal, Vancouver and Toronto get extremely busy at this\r\ntime of the year, though the country is quieter the remoter you travel. Almost\r\nall national parks of the country are heaving with tourists in the summer\r\nmonths because it is vacation time for kids and they are out in full strength\r\nwith their families exploring around. The accommodation rates do go up in these\r\nmonths; so it makes sense for you to close your booking several months ahead.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><br style=\"text-align: start;\">\r\n</span><br style=\"text-align: start;\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">How long does it take to get a Canadian visa?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">As you\r\nsift through&nbsp;<span style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:inherit;\r\nfont-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"></span><span class=\"bold\">Canada travel packages</span></span><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">, you should be aware of the time required to get a Canadian\r\nvisa. You can apply for the visa on the Government of Canada website, where you\r\nneed to fill in two application forms. Attach the mandatory support documents\r\nand once you have checked the form for its completion, you can submit the same.\r\nAfter the embassy verifies your details, it will call you for an interview. The\r\nprocessing of the application takes between 10-15 days from the date on which\r\nyou had applied. You can check your visa status online.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><br style=\"text-align: start;\">\r\n</span><br style=\"text-align: start;\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">which is the whale-watching season in Canada?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">Head to\r\nBritish Colombia to see Orcas, known for the world’s highest population of the\r\nKiller Whales. Also spot humpback whales, grey whales and minke whales. Come\r\nhere between April and October for the best sighting. Quebec also has a sizable\r\npopulation of Minkes, Belugas and humpback whales, but you can also spot the\r\nblue whale, the largest known mammal on the planet and the fin whale here from\r\nMay through October. Visit Newfoundland and Labrador to spot the rarer spotted\r\nwhale apart from the minke and sperm whales. May through September is the best\r\ntime for it. Nova Scotia and New Brunswick are also great for whale-watching\r\naround the same time of the year.</span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><span class=\"bold\"><b><span style=\"border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:\r\nnone windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">What are the popular events and festivals\r\nof Canada?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">A\r\nveritable cultural landscape, Canada is known for its multi-cultural ethnicity\r\nand the resultant diversity in its art and culture scene. The International\r\nFringe Theatre Festival in Edmonton is the oldest and the largest fringe\r\ntheatre festival in the world to take place every August. Montreal’s Jazz\r\nFestival needs no introduction as does the Toronto Film Festival. The Jazz\r\nfestival is an annual event that kicks off late June and continues for 11 days.\r\nOntario’s Stratford Festival is also a popular one for it is the world’s\r\nlargest classical repertory theatre.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><br style=\"text-align: start;\">\r\n</span><br style=\"text-align: start;\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">What is Calgary Stampede and when does it happen?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">Calgary\r\nStampede is a yearly rodeo show held every July in Calgary, Alberta. The rodeo\r\nevent is a mix of shows, exhibitions and festival that pans out over 10 days\r\nand bills itself as ‘the greatest outdoor show on earth’. There are millions of\r\nvisitors every year who come to witness one of the world’s largest rodeos,\r\naside from parades, concerts, stage shows, chuckwagon racing, agricultural\r\ncompetitions, among other exhibits.</span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><span class=\"bold\"><b><span style=\"border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:\r\nnone windowtext 0in;padding:0in\">What activities can I pursue in Banff,\r\nCanada?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">A part\r\nof the Banff National Park in Canada’s Alberta region, it is regarded as the\r\ncountry’s best adventure destination. With a Rocky-mountain-dominating skyline,\r\nat Banff you can ride the Banff Gondola to the Sulphur Mountain, go hiking or\r\nskiing in the Sunshine Village, go whitewater rafting on the Kicking Horse\r\nRiver, visit Lake Moraine during sunrise, drive the famous Icefields Parkway or\r\ngo hiking on the Athabasca Glacier. The Banff Avenue has its share of\r\nchateau-style resorts, cool cafes, and souvenir boutiques.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><br style=\"text-align: start;\">\r\n</span><br style=\"text-align: start;\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">What is Vancouver most famous for?</span><o:p></o:p></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">The bustling\r\nseaport city in British Colombia, Vancouver is atmospheric, artsy and a\r\ntreasure-trove of cultural and architectural gems, outside of sporting a\r\nharbour-side charm all year round. When in Vancouver visit the national\r\nhistorical site, the 400-acre Stanley Park. You also need to round up the\r\nVancouver Aquarium, Seawall - a 28 km waterfront path that takes you through\r\nsome of the best sites in the city, Downtown and West End for its beaches,\r\nGastown and Granville Island apart from the quaint Chinatown neighborhood.</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"><br style=\"text-align: start;\"></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span class=\"bold\"><span itemprop=\"name\" style=\"font-style:inherit;font-variant:\r\ninherit;font-stretch: inherit;line-height:inherit\"><b><span itemprop=\"mainEntity\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Question\" style=\"font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; text-align: start;\">Which is the best time to visit the Niagara Falls in Canada?</span></b></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;\r\nmso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;padding:0in\"><span class=\"bold\"><span class=\"fontcol-3c3\">Niagara\r\nFalls in Ontario in Canada receives the highest footfalls in the summer months\r\nof June and August because the mist and the breeze from the waterfall cools\r\ndown the surroundings somewhat, and is a breather for the travelers out\r\nsightseeing on foot all day. The free-of-cost Discover Niagara Shuttle is in\r\nfull operation in this season. The spring and the fall brings in fewer tourists\r\nbecause of the drop in temperatures before it entirely freezes over in the\r\nwinter. The Maid of the Mist boat tours are quite popular in the high season as\r\nit gives you a sense of the volume and the impact of the falls.</span><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>', 'Visit Canada in 10 days is a perfect combination of beautiful landscapes and popular cities of the region, visiting Vancouver & Calgary, famous Jasper including the Banff National Parks.', '49.2827,123.1207', '1', 'APR OCT NOV', 'Adventurous', '02nd April 2022', '2022/04/02', '2022/04/12', '2022/03/01', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><u><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-font-kerning:18.0pt\">10 days Canada Tour Package<o:p></o:p></span></u></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Visit Canada&nbsp;in 10 days&nbsp;is a perfect combination of beautiful\r\nlandscapes and popular cities of the region, visiting Vancouver &amp; Calgary, famous&nbsp;Jasper\r\nincluding the Banff National Parks.</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 1: ARRIVE VANCOUVER – Sightseeing of Vancouver</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Visit the historic district of Vancouver, Gastown the curiosity of\r\nGastown,&nbsp;the famous Steam Clock is perfect place in the city’s atmosphere\r\nand capture typical Victorian</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Also visit famous Chinatown &amp; Dr. Sun Yat-Sen’s&nbsp;Chinese\r\nGarden, the first Chinese garden in the world to be built away from China.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Visit Vancouver’s must-see attraction,&nbsp;Fly Over Canada,&nbsp;which\r\ntakes you to&nbsp;Canada in 4D (not in 10 days but in 8 minutes!), Comfortably\r\nseated in&nbsp;dynamic seats.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Spend a relaxing afternoon at Stanley Park,&nbsp;Vancouver’s\r\nlargest park.&nbsp;You can explore it&nbsp;on foot or by bike, a walk of 9 km’s\r\nmakes the tour.&nbsp;In both cases, do not miss to go to the&nbsp;Amerindian\r\ntotem pole&nbsp;and from the point of view to&nbsp;admire the Lions Gate\r\nBridge.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Evening admire the sunset,&nbsp;Vancouver’s best spot is&nbsp;atop\r\nthe Vancouver Lookout.&nbsp;In the same style as the CN Tower in Toronto, the\r\nbuilding has an&nbsp;observation platform&nbsp;at 170 meters to admire a 360 °\r\npanorama of the entire city.</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">And to finish in style, this first day in Vancouver,&nbsp;heading\r\nto the Yale town district, where are concentrated&nbsp;the best restaurants in\r\nthe city.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 2: In VANCOUVER:</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Continue visiting Canada:&nbsp;a flyover from Vancouver 20 minutes\r\nby seaplane.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">visit the morning on Granville Island, find lots of&nbsp;vintage\r\nshops and local crafts&nbsp;a huge indoor market.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Later in the afternoon,cultural visit to the Museum of\r\nAnthropology&nbsp;to understand&nbsp;the history of the Native American peoples\r\nof British Columbia and Canada.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Exit the museum &amp; take a tour by&nbsp;the beach of Wreck Beach.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Visit Van Elsen Botanical Garden the most beautiful gardens in\r\nNorth America, having more than 7,500 species of plants and trees.&nbsp;Wooden\r\nbridges, waterfalls, fountains.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 3: Whistler</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Early drive&nbsp;of 2 hours from Vancouver to Whistler, it’s known\r\nfor some of the best&nbsp;ski&nbsp;slopes in the world the perfect place to\r\nenjoy winter sports&nbsp;in Canada.&nbsp;You can also go&nbsp;on dog sled rides&nbsp;or&nbsp;snowmobiling.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Visit the Peak gondola and enjoy a superb panoramic breathtaking\r\nview of the valley and the glacier.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 4-5: Wells Gray Provincial Park</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Early drive from Whistler to arrive the park by afternoon its\r\ndrive about 5 &amp; ½ to 6 hours. A must stop for all routes in Western Canada which\r\nallows a truly beautiful place in western Canada wilder-park.</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">The road from Whistler to Wells Gray&nbsp;is Highway 99&nbsp;and considered&nbsp;as\r\none of the most beautiful roads in Canada&nbsp;and really worth driving. Later Visit\r\nHelm ken Fall a must-see site of Wells Gray.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Do not miss Bailey’s Chute&nbsp;to witness salmon’s going against river\r\nalso visit Spahat Falls&nbsp;&amp; Dawson Falls.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Also take a wonderful Hike through the beautiful flowery meadows\r\nalong the trails to Trophy Mountain&nbsp;leads to Sheila Lake&nbsp;for sumptuous\r\nlandscapes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 6: Jasper National Park</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Jasper National Park enlisted in UNESCO World Heritage is drive of\r\n4 hours, On the way stop at&nbsp;Mount Robson witness the highest Canadian\r\nRockies peak. Arrive famous&nbsp;Jasper National Park and visit the 2 beautiful\r\nlakes Maligns, It is&nbsp;the largest rocky lake&nbsp;and&nbsp;Spirit Island\r\nwalk around or enjoy&nbsp;a cruise&nbsp;on the lake, On the way back visit&nbsp;Medicine\r\nLake,&nbsp;the second lake to be seen in Jasper National Park.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 7: In Jasper National Park</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Explore the National Park hiking,&nbsp;Jasper offers&nbsp;different&nbsp;level\r\nof trails such as “Maligns Canyon” “Cavell Meadows”&nbsp;“Sulfur Skyline” elevation\r\n700 m&nbsp;offers a magnificent 360 ° view of the Rockies.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">“Old Fort” amazing view of the Athabasca River<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Later evening visit another must-see place in Jasper,&nbsp;“Miette\r\nHot spring” hot water&nbsp;outside enjoying a&nbsp;magnificent view of the park\r\nand the mountains.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 8: Banff National Park</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Another most scenic drives in Canada via highway 93 will connect\r\nthe cities of Jasper to Banff, visit Athabasca Falls,&nbsp;over 20 meters high,\r\npause at Sunwapta Falls, witness Columbia Ice field and the Athabasca Glacier choose\r\npopular activities like a glacier walk on foot or&nbsp;on giant tires&nbsp;for\r\na bus ride.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Overnight at Lake Louise&nbsp;the closest town to&nbsp;Lake Louise&nbsp;is\r\nintense turquoise blue, the lake is simply splendid also most photographed lakes.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 9: Hiking in Banff National park</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Hiking options to Lake Louise, Moraine Lake the second famous Banff\r\nLake, Or Plaine des Six Glaciers allows a series of impressive glaciers and\r\npeaks.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Day 10: Calgary</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Drive approx. 2 hours to Calgary&nbsp;visit&nbsp;Glenbow Museum\r\nperfect information about the history of the region of Alberta it’s the largest\r\nart museum in Western Canada.&nbsp;His visit is really very interesting.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Also visit Calgary Tower,&nbsp;Calgary’s iconic landmark the tower\r\noffers&nbsp;a 360 ° view of the entire city and part of the Canadian\r\nRockies.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Later afternoon visit&nbsp;Heritage Park Village walk through\r\na&nbsp;typical western Canadian village,&nbsp;Browse&nbsp;stalls, the forge and\r\nthe bakery to discover the lifestyles of yesteryears.&nbsp;Witness paddle boat&nbsp;cruise\r\nan authentic&nbsp;steam locomotive.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"