(88, 1, '2 Days PETRA EXPRESS TOUR (US$.500)', '2-Days-PETRA-EXPRESS-TOUR-(US$.500)', 'package-main-photo-61c539b0b3001.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Do I need\r\na visa for Jordan?<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Most likely, yes. For some travelers,\r\na visa can be obtained on arrival (no longer available at the Wadi Araba border\r\ncrossing). It is best to check the&nbsp;Jordan Tourism Board’s visa info page&nbsp;to\r\ndetermine if citizens of your country need to obtain a visa before arrival or\r\nif you can get one on arrival.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>What\r\ncurrency is used?</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">The Jordanian dinar (JD) One JD is approximately 1.4 USD which keeps\r\nfluctuating. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>How do I\r\nget to Jordan?</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">By air:&nbsp;</span></strong>There are\r\ntwo international airports in Jordan: Queen Alia International Airport in Amman\r\nand King Hussein International Airport in Aqaba. If you are traveling from\r\noutside the Middle East, Amman is your best bet.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">By\r\nland:&nbsp;</span></strong>If you are coming from neighboring Israel or\r\nthe Palestinian Territories, you have three border crossing options for\r\narriving in Jordan: King Hussein Bridge in the north, the Allenby Bridge near\r\nthe Dead Sea, or Wadi Araba on the Red Sea. Be sure to double check visa\r\nrequirements, exit taxes, as these are subject to change.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>What is\r\nthe best time of the year - season - to visit Jordan?<o:p></o:p></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><span style=\"color: rgb(111, 111, 111);\">Best time to visit Jordan would be during March and May, and\r\nSeptember to November. Jordan climate in general can be very hot during June -\r\nAugust, and very cold during December to February.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Is Jordan\r\nexpensive?</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">It depends. If you are on a budget,\r\nyou can find affordable local meals — like a falafel sandwich — for a couple\r\ndinars or less, and stay in budget accommodations, like hostels in Amman and\r\nBedouin camps in Wadi Rum for around $20-30 per night. If you’d prefer more\r\nupscale dining options and creature comforts, you will find an array of\r\nrestaurant options with extensive local and international menus in Amman.\r\nLuxury hotels in Amman, Dead Sea, Petra, and Aqaba run around $100-$300+ per\r\nnight. There are mid-range options&nbsp;as well, for around $100 per night.\r\nWhether you are traveling on a budget or planning to indulge, keep in mind that\r\nthe typical cost per day for a tour is about $125-300.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>How do I\r\nget around Jordan?</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Visitors to Jordan tend to travel by car — either self-driving a\r\nrented car or hiring a car and driver. Public transportation in Jordan can be\r\nunreliable and there are no trains. If renting a car, keep in mind that driving\r\nin Jordan may be quite different from driving at home. Drivers tend to be\r\naggressive. In many places, there are no lines on the road, and even if they\r\nexist, people often ignore them. Road signs are not always posted and GPS may\r\nnot be accurate. If you find driving in Jordan exhausting, ask our specialists\r\nabout booking you a driver and guide so you can sit back, and enjoy the\r\nspectacular scenery.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">If you are traveling from Amman to Wadi Rum or Aqaba, you may\r\nconsider a domestic flight from Queen Alia International Airport in Amman to\r\nKing Hussein International Airport in Aqaba.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align:justify\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>', 'Intro\r\nIn 2 days PETRA EXPRESS TOUR will discover PETRA the Rose Red City lost for centuries to the outside world & Explore the majestic desert of Wadi Rum valley.', '30.3285,35.4444', '1', 'MAR APR OCT', 'Easy', '02nd April 2022', '2022/04/02', '2022/04/04', '2022/03/31', NULL, '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;text-transform:uppercase\">DAY 1: ARRIVAL - WADI\r\nRUM - LITTLE PETRA - PETRA.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Meet &amp; assist\r\nat Aqaba port or King Hussein airport by our representative and transfer to\r\nWadi Rum.<br>\r\nEnjoy the wilderness adventure of a 4×4 jeep tour of Wadi Rum, following in the\r\nfootsteps of Lawrence of Arabia.<br>\r\nThen drive to&nbsp;visit&nbsp;&nbsp;Al Beidha, better known as Little Petra.\r\nLittle Petra was an important suburb of Petra, the entry and exit point for the\r\ntrade routes to the north and north-west.<br>\r\nArrival to your hotel in Petra for overnight.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin;text-transform:\r\nuppercase\">DAY 2: PETRA – PETRA VISIT - DEPARTURE</span></b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">After breakfast, visit Petra the home of the Nabataea’s; the\r\ncomplete city carved in a mountain with the huge colorful rocks that called\r\n“the red rose city” the tour will start by crossing the “Sig” lined with\r\nmountains in multiple colors up to the treasury; the pride of all Jordanian, the\r\nroyal tomb, theater, the high place of sacrifice and roman soldier tombs.<br style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent !important;\">\r\nThen drive to Aqaba port, Araba Border or King Hussein Airport for departure<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>TOUR COST US$.500/ (SUBJECT TO CHANGE) E. &amp;. E. O.</b></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\"><b>Optional Tours:</b><br></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Petra by Night<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">The excursion\r\ndeparts from Petra visitors center every Monday, Wednesday and Thursday evening\r\nat 20:30, returning to the visitors center around 22:30. tickets are&nbsp;US$ 24.00\r\nper person, children under 12 years are free of charge.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">Petra Kitchen<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\">On one of the\r\nnights while you are in Petra you can enjoy a night cuisine course and meal at\r\nthe Petra kitchen.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Calibri, &quot;sans-serif&quot;; font-size: 11pt;\">The price for this\r\ncooking course is&nbsp;US50$ per person.</span></p>', 500, '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\r\ncolor:#595959;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in;\r\npadding:0in\">Privacy policy</span><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\r\n&quot;Arial&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#29293A\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; backgrou